CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 6, 1965, p. 24, reads: "Schenley Favored to Win City Cage Crown Friday - City Title Up For Grabs - These players will carry th banners of Schenley and South Hills High Schools, Friday, at Pitt Field House, in the battle for the City League basketball championship...   In the right photo, members of the South Hill club discuss strategy with Coach Bruce Weston, kneeling, left.  Team members are, standing: Tony Chiocca, Alvin Rue, Bill Schleicher and Nate Snyder.  Kneeling: Don Allen, Craig Phillips and John Mende. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Members of South Hills High School basketball team, kneeling from left: coach Bruce Weston, Don Allen, Craig Phillips, John Mende; standing: Tony Chiocca, Alvin Rue, Bill Schleicher, and Nate Snyder
